description: The shipment is delivered to a designated location inside the recipient's door. The maximum weight per package carried in (package or pallet that is split up) is 35kg.  In order for the delivery to be carried out, free and unobstructed access to the specified location is required, and for deliveries more than four (4) floors up, an elevator must be available. The customer is responsible for protecting delicate flooring prior to delivery. If the conditions are not met, delivery will be performed without carrying indoors. Any further delivery attempts (in case of unsuccessful delivery on the first attempt) will be carried out without carrying indoors.

description: Agreed delivery entails that we against a surcharge agree on time of delivery with the recipient in advance. This additional service must always be booked if the recipient stays at a private or unattended address. Otherwise optionally available.  We contact the recipient the day before delivery to agree on the delivery time, and the driver calls the recipient 30-60 minutes upon delivery to ensure that someone is present.
For those who would like to get the shipment delivered already on Saturday between 10:00-16:00.

Bring leaves the shipment at the recipient's address without the recipient being there to accept it.  This additional service entails that the sender accepts the associated risk with regard to liability and surrenders the right to compensation from Bring in the event of damage and loss. The shipment is registered as delivered so that it can be tracked. The GPS coordinates are registered as the delivery address.

We also offer a frost-free service for an additional fee. The service does not come with a temperature guarantee. Yet, we strive to ensure that the carrier keeps the shipment frost-free at a temperature above 0 degrees Celsius.

To send dangerous goods we need to know what type of goods you are sending. You can search for either ADR number or type of goods for example "nitro".  After finishing the order, print one label and waybill in four copies. Pin together the waybills and attach them and the label on the goods. If you wish to send goods in categories that you cannot find on our pages, such as explosives or radioactive substances, call Customer Service (Bookings) on 04045 for assistance.

description: Label free provides the ability to send parcels without a label, and is useful for senders who do not have access to a printer.   A unique code in the format BRING-1234-5678 is sent to the sender by e-mail after the booking is completed. This code, as well as the recipient's name and address, is written on the parcel before it is handed in. A supplement QR-code is also requested along with the label free code. This QR-code can be scanned by the staff to print a label which is attached to the parcel.

Some destinations offer even faster delivery at an additional cost. Contact your local Bring office for more information.

Mailbox Parcel (Pakke i postkassen) is a parcel that will be delivered in the recipient’s mailbox. If the parcel for various reasons does not fit in the mailbox, the sender may choose to leave the parcel on the door handle (in a special bag) to avoid it being sent to the pickup point.  This service can be ordered either by the sender at time of booking, or selected by the recipient before receiving the parcel. Sender is able to use VAS 1280 to reserve against the recipient either adding or removing this additional service. When the parcel is delivered the bar code is scanned and the recipient will receive a notification. Note that if the parcel is delivered in the mailbox the additional fee will not occur.
For those who need to send goods between 08-25 degrees. The shipment must be packed in such a way that it can withstand exposure to cold for up to 2 hours.
